dcterms:description: ERA5 is a state-of-the-art atmospheric reanalysis dataset that combines observations from various sources with a numerical weather model to create a comprehensive representation of the Earth’s atmosphere. The dataset provides daily total precipitation data at a horizontal resolution of 0.25°.
dcterms:title: ERA5

dcterms:description: GFDL-ESM4 is a state-of-the-art Earth System Model that provides daily precipitation data from the first ensemble member of the historical simulation. The dataset spans from 1850 to 2014, with a spatial resolution of 1° latitude and 1.25° longitude.
dcterms:title: GFDL-ESM4

dcterms:creator: A. J. Cannon
S. R. Sobie
T. Q. Murdock
dcterms:description: Quantile Mapping (QM) is a statistical method used for bias correction of climate model precipitation. It aligns the estimated cumulative distribution of model output with observed precipitation patterns over a reference time period.
dcterms:title: Quantile Mapping (QM)
